The Chinese mainland recorded 129 confirmed COVID-19 cases on Saturday, with 87 attributed to local transmissions and 42 from overseas, data from the National Health Commission showed on Sunday. A total of 853 asymptomatic cases were also recorded on Saturday, and 6,288 asymptomatic patients remain under medical observation. The cumulative number of confirmed cases on the Chinese mainland is 228,648, with the death toll from COVID-19 standing at 5,226. The latest tally of confirmed cases in the Hong Kong and Macao special administrative regions and Taiwan region is as follows: Hong Kong: 349,976 (66,506 recoveries, 9,461 deaths) Macao: 783 (413 recoveries, six deaths) Taiwan: 4,408,857 (13,742 recoveries, 8,531 deaths)